By Aminu Garko The Presidential Candidate of New Nigeria People’s Party (NNPP), Rabiu Kwankwaso has expressed optimism of winning the ongoing presidential election.  The News Agency of Nigeria ( NAN) reports that Kwankwaso spoke shortly after casting his vote about 11.45a.m. at Tandu 1 Kwankwasu Ward in Madobi Local Government of Kano State .  ” I will win the election by the special Grace of Allah,” Kwankwaso said. He called for more political tolerance and understanding among politicians for a better electoral process in the country.  ” We must demonstrate high sense of political tolerance to ensure peaceful conduct of future exercise,” he said. (NAN)